The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Loose Change
                                                                                                                 LOOSE CHANGE
                              
	 ICICI Prudential Life has launched a single premium lifelong Ulip  Wealth Advantage. The plan allows consumers stay invested for their entire lifetime, even beyond the age of 70 years. The scheme offers the flexibility to increase or decrease the sum assured, according to an individuals needs. There is also the option to withdraw money systematically through the automatic withdrawal plan from the sixth year of the policy.                            
	 Tata AIG Life Insurance and South Indian Bank have entered into a pact. Tata AIG policy-holders will now be able to pay their premium in cash or cheque at any of the 520 core-banking solutions branches of the South Indian Bank.                             
	 Citibank has launched an online money transfer service  Citi Online Remit  for US-based non-resident Indians. The facility will enable NRIs to directly transfer funds to India from any US checking or savings account or using a US credit or debit card.                            
	 Punjab National Bank has launched two kinds of global credit cards  Global Gold and Global Classic  for different income groups. The cards will offer a free credit period of up to 50 days, no annual fee and attractive reward points.                                                                                                                               
